---

## 1. Overview

This project implements and verifies a 5-stage pipelined RV32I processor core using a structured SystemVerilog/UVM verification environment. The design has evolved from a basic pipeline into a latency-tolerant CPU subsystem with external instruction/data memory interfaces, a variable-latency memory transaction unit, and a verified instruction/data cache hierarchy.

The primary focus is CPU design verification. The testbench validates architectural correctness using commit-trace monitoring, an independent scoreboard/reference model, coverage-driven program generation, directed cache stress sequences, cache statistics, and protocol-level SystemVerilog assertions.

| Development Phase | Scope | Status |
|---|---|---|
| Phase 1 | Modular RTL refactor into reusable CPU blocks | Complete |
| Phase 2 | External instruction/data memory interfaces and variable-latency memory transaction unit | Complete |
| Phase 3 | Direct-mapped I-cache, write-through D-cache, cache stress testing, coverage, and assertions | Complete |

---

