## 3. Processor Features

### 3.1 ISA Support

The core supports a verification-oriented RV32I subset that exercises integer execution, memory access, and control-flow behavior.

| Instruction Class | Supported Instructions |
|---|---|
| Integer immediate | ADDI, ANDI, ORI, XORI |
| Register-register ALU | ADD, SUB, AND, OR, XOR |
| Upper immediate | LUI, AUIPC |
| Memory | LW, SW |
| Control flow | BEQ, BNE, JAL, JALR |

### 3.2 Pipeline Microarchitecture

- Classic 5-stage in-order pipeline: IF, ID, EX, MEM, WB.
- Single-issue, in-order commit model.
- Architectural x0 register hardwired to zero.
- Pipeline valid-bit tracking to support bubbles, redirects, and stalls.
- EX-stage branch and jump redirect handling.
- Commit-stage observability for UVM scoreboarding and coverage.

### 3.3 Hazard Handling

| Hazard Type | Implemented Handling |
|---|---|
| RAW ALU dependency | EX/MEM and MEM/WB forwarding |
| Load-use dependency | One-cycle stall/bubble insertion |
| Taken branch | EX-stage redirect and younger instruction flush |
| JAL/JALR | Redirect to computed target and pipeline flush |
| Variable-latency memory | Pipeline held through memory transaction unit until response returns |

---

